music_lights.py can be used for playing a .wav file and simultaneously controlling up to 3 Philips Hue lights according
to the most prominent notes in each 3-second interval of the song. 

Requirements:
python 2.7
mingus >= 0.4.2.3
phue >= 0.7

Command line:
python music_lights.py -f filename.wav -n number_of_lights -i hue_bridge_ip

Development in progress...
